  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 12:59 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] Copy Flow Finally Produced a Dispersed Sample\n\n**Task:** Check whether any recent PM copy sample escaped crowd-latching and became informational enough to use as an overlay.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Ran `scripts/copy-intel-tracker.py`; HL leaderboard consensus flipped back to **BTC 7L/2S bullish, ETH 6L/1S bullish, SOL 4L/5S bearish**.\n- Pulled the latest 50 PM copy fills from `logs/pm-copy.log`.\n- Latest sample was **18 bullish / 32 bearish** across **10 unique titles**.\n- Concentration was far lower than the earlier Apr 22 crowd-pile events:\n  - dominant title share = **10 / 50 = 0.20**\n  - top-two title share = **19 / 50 = 0.38**\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v8k-copy-dispersion-informational-threshold.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the first recent sample that actually cleared the anti-crowding ladder instead of failing it. The flow still leaned bearish, but it was spread across enough titles that it reads more like broad positioning than one expiry cluster reflexively dogpiling.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the crowding ladder intact.\n- Add a new working rule: copy flow is only eligible as a weak overlay when dominant-title share is below **0.40** and top-two title share is below **0.40**.\n- Do not let dispersed flow create trades by itself.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, measure whether dispersed copy samples align with local tape better than concentrated samples, so we can decide if this overlay deserves any weight at all.\n\n\n## 2026-04-22 12:58 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Convert Wrong-Side Classification into a Staged Pipeline\n\n**Task:** Use the full 12h tape to move from isolated wrong-side labels toward a real research pipeline that escalates from suspicion to confirmed session rejection.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- The 12h tape now shows a complete progression:\n  - pinned price at `0.505 / 0.495`\n  - repeated wrong-sided direction through YES-only skips\n  - no meaningful price excursion first\n  - later regime confirmation with `TREND`\n- The clean confirmation window appeared by roughly **12:13-12:18 UTC**, after directional persistence had already been obvious for several minutes.\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v8j-wrong-side-classifier-pipeline.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis should not stay as a single stop rule. The tape naturally separates into stages: first the session looks suspicious, then structurally wrong-sided, then regime-confirmed, and only then fully rejectable. That is a better pipeline because it tells us not just what the session is, but when conviction should increase.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Add a staged wrong-side pipeline:\n  1. directional persistence watch\n  2. structural classification\n  3. regime confirmation\n  4. hard stop\n- Keep trend-aligned and inversion paths separate inside that pipeline.\n\n**",
